@node chips.amber "Amber Hardware Stats"
@version 0.275
@toc chipset.index

    Amber Hardware Stats


            Amber is the de-interlacer chip found in the A3000. It
        contains 2 megabytes of 30ns Static RAM, and is capable of
        operating with 12 BITs of data.

                          PART       VIDEO      CHIP TYPE
                Amber   390538-03   NTSC/PAL      PLCC

            - VGA DB15 connector
            - compatible with NTSC-M, PAL-B, PAL-G, and PAL-H
                - NTSC 31.47 kHz horizontal unbypassed
                - NTSC 15.73 kHz horizontal bypassed
                - PAL 21.25 kHz horizontal unbypassed
                - PAL 15.625 kHz horizontal bypassed
                - NTSC 60 Hz vertical
                - PAL 50 Hz vertical
            - NTSC 35ns wide, 910 pixels per line
            - PAL 35ns wide, 908 pixels per line
            - supports overscan and severe overscan modes
            - supports scan doubling
            - external enable/disable toggle switch
            - 12 BIT capable buffer

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

    PART NUMBERS (not in FAQ):

        390538-03   Amber
        318069-02   Agnus 8372
        318069-03   Agnus 8372a
        314874-01   IC Extractor for Fat Agnus


    JUMPERS:

        A2000:J101      enable address 19 of 68000
        A2000:J500      EXRAM signal

        A500:JP2        enable address 19 of 68000

        A3000:J200
        A3000:J482
        A3000:J351
        A3000:J483
