@node ocs "OCS - Original Chip Set"
@version 0.121
@toc chipset.index

    Original Chip Set

        @{"     " link screenmodes.ocs  } Screenmodes
        @{"     " link colormodes.ocs   } Colormodes
        @{"     " link stats.ocs        } Hardware Stats

            The OCS chips originated in 1985 and were designed by the
        original Amiga crew of Los Gatos, California. These people
        included Jay Miner (Father of the Amiga) and RJ Michael. In its
        day OCS was the most advanced graphics set available on any home
        computer.

@endnode
